SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT province_name) FROM location;
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT town_name) FROM location;
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT location_type) FROM location;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM location;

Results:
- 5 unique provinces
- 25 unique towns
- 2 location types (Urban and Rural)
- 39,650 total locations

Thabo has successfully queried the location table and discovered its geographic scope. He used SELECT * with LIMIT to preview the data, then used COUNT(DISTINCT) to understand the distribution of provinces, towns, and location types. He correctly observed that with 60,000 visits and 39,650 locations, multiple visits must be recorded for many locations. He understands the location table stores geographic information across 5 provinces and 25 towns in both urban and rural areas.

